---
/**
 * domain-agent-design 0001 · Figure 2 — "Boundary → surface".
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from
 * docs/domain-agent-design/lessons/0001-the-domain-agent-design-method.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption incl. the footnote <sup id="r3">). Lives as an
 * .astro component for the same reason as Fig1. References the #arwM arrowhead,
 * embedded as a local <defs> so url(#arwM) resolves inside this svg.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 230"
        role="img"
        aria-label="The responsibility boundary defines what actions the agent owns; the tool surface is the set of tools that implement it, and each added tool widens both capability and blast radius."
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arwM"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#3d54c9"></path></marker
            >
        </defs>
        <text x="320" y="18" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >Draw the boundary first, then fit the surface to it</text
        >

        <!-- boundary -->
        <rect
            x="40"
            y="40"
            width="240"
            height="150"
            rx="12"
            fill="#eceef9"
            stroke="#3d54c9"
            stroke-width="2"></rect>
        <text x="160" y="60" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#3d54c9"
            >1 &middot; Responsibility boundary</text
        >
        <text x="160" y="82" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#111110"
            >OWNS: answer, draft, small refund</text
        >
        <text x="160" y="98" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#111110"
            >DEFERS: large refund &rarr; human</text
        >
        <text x="160" y="114" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#9a2417"
            >REFUSES: legal / medical advice</text
        >
        <text x="160" y="130" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#9a2417"
            >REFUSES: anything outside support</text
        >
        <text x="160" y="166" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" font-style="italic" fill="#6b675f"
            >the contract: what's in, what's out</text
        >

        <line x1="280" y1="115" x2="356" y2="115" stroke="#3d54c9" marker-end="url(#arwM)"></line>
        <text x="318" y="108" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" fill="#6b675f">implies</text>

        <!-- surface -->
        <rect
            x="360"
            y="40"
            width="240"
            height="150"
            rx="12"
            fill="#f4f4f6"
            stroke="#6b675f"
            stroke-width="1.4"></rect>
        <text x="480" y="60" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >2 &middot; Tool surface (smallest that fits)</text
        >
        <rect x="378" y="72" width="204" height="18" rx="4" fill="#e9f3ec" stroke="#2f5d3a"></rect>
        <text x="480" y="85" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#2f5d3a"
            >read order &middot; read account &middot; search KB &mdash; zero blast</text
        >
        <rect x="378" y="96" width="204" height="18" rx="4" fill="#fdf3e7" stroke="#c2700f"></rect>
        <text x="480" y="109" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#c2700f"
            >issue refund &mdash; bounded write</text
        >
        <rect x="378" y="120" width="204" height="18" rx="4" fill="#fbecec" stroke="#9a2417"></rect>
        <text x="480" y="133" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#9a2417"
            >escalate to human &mdash; hand-off</text
        >
        <text x="480" y="166" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" font-style="italic" fill="#6b675f"
            >each tool = more capability + more blast radius</text
        >
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        The <b>tool surface</b>
        <em>is</em> the agent's reach.<sup><a href="#s3" id="r3">3</a></sup> Fit the smallest surface
        that covers the boundary: every tool you add widens what the agent can do &mdash; and what can
        go wrong if it's confused, jailbroken, or looping. A tool you didn't add is blast radius you don't
        carry.
    </figcaption>
</figure>
